Blocks.Text: INDICATION: Proteinuria, and each kidney biopsy.
After obtaining written consent the patient is CT scan of the prone position was
performed. The right kidney was targeted for biopsy. Lower pole was accessed
using an 18-gauge coaxial needle after sterilely prepping and draping the skin.
Multiple cores 18-gauge in size 2 cm in length were obtained from the lower
pole. There is a small hematoma surrounding the biopsy site. There were no
significant complications. Patient targeted the procedure well.
Successful CT-guided kidney biopsy of the right kidney lower pole..
